Jamie Murray's men's doubles campaign ended in the third round as the British doubles expert and John Peers suffered defeat at the Australian Open on Monday.

Murray and Peers edged a tight first set but fourth seeds Ivan Dodig and Marcelo Melo fought back to triumph 6-7 (8-10), 6-2, 6-4.

Despite his previous mixed doubles success, winning the title at Wimbledon in 2007, Murray was bidding to reach the last eight of a slam in men's doubles for only the second time.

