Breaks were exchanged in the first set and the British/Australian combination saved two set points in the tiebreak before taking it 10-8.

As the planes roared overhead for the Australia Day air show in Melbourne, Dodig and Melo hit back and quickly took the second set to level the match.

Dodig and Melo then broke for 3-2 in the deciding set as Murray dumped a smash into the net and one break proved enough for the Croatian and Brazilian duo to clinch victory.

